2. Educative cooperation in upper secondary education

The parties decide to implement initiatives which promote exchanges and cooperation between both educational systems through:

- Promoting exchanges of classes, recent graduate teachers and school leaders between the two countries, in all levels;

- Collaboration in the area of teacher training and job-shadowing by promoting and encouraging mobility of teaching staff and exchange of trainee teachers and teacher training between the two countries;

Supporting and encouraging partnerships between French and Danish schools;

Welcoming and sharing of innovative teaching methods

Encouraging class exchanges and also individual pupil mobility in secondary schools, general and vocational schools;

The Parties agree to work together to build a European Education Area stepping up mobility and exchanges, multilinguism and harmonisation of educational systems. The Parties will encourage all the institutions to participate in the Erasmust program.

3. Exchanges of best practices

The Parties intent to share good practices and views on common interest topics, especially in:

Soliciting regular meetings between senior staff level and study visits;

Sharing information concerning educational policies and reforms in both countries;

Exchanging expertise, resources, good practices in the priority fields as digital education, inclusive education and integration of students with disabilities and add value to vocational field

4. Institutional cooperation and Action Plan

The cooperation proposal mentioned in the present Letter of Intent will be featured in a joint action plan elaborated by the Danish Ministry of Education and the French Institute of Denmark.

Signed in Copenhagen, March 1st 2018, in two (2) originals in the French and English languages, each:

